FBIS4-65383 "drweu095_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-095 Daily Report 16 May 1994 SPAIN Solana Welcomes EU Support for Bosnia Peace Plan Solana Welcomes EU Support for Bosnia Peace Plan LD1605224094 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 2100 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605224094 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Spanish BFN [Text] [Announcer] Over to the Balkan crisis. The fighting continues around the Bosnian city of Tuzla that was attacked after the Muslim forces said that they had made territorial gains at the Serbs' expense. Meanwhile, diplomatic initiatives to end the war continue. The European Union [EU] foreign ministers have shown their support for the international plan agreed on last week, describing it as the only realistic way to end the conflict. From Brussels, here is our correspondent Nacho Hernandez. [Hernandez] The EU supports the agreement reached at the Geneva meeting on Bosnia-Herzegovina despite its rejection by the parties in conflict. The Twelve see the fact that Russia, the United States, the United Nations, and the EU have a unified position in Bosnia-Herzegovina as a positive move. Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana said that for the first time positions are coordinated. [Begin Solana recording] If we are able to make this so by focusing all of our energies on it over the next few days. I repeat that the agreement that was reached with all the concerned parties is something we have been wishing for a good many months. [end recording] [Hernandez] Furthermore, the Twelve have decided to grant the city of Mostar aid worth 7,500 million pesetas. The EU starts to administer the city of Mostar on 1 June.
